title: Why I wouldn't invest in open-source companies, even though I ran one.
excerpt: After more than 12.000 Github stars, two successful open-source projects, a failed open-core company, and a successful prop-tech one*, I feel more than ever that giving your product away for free is just as bad a business strategy as it sounds.
